Analysis, and Visualization, of Quantitative Client Feedback Survey

by John Akwei, Data Science Specialist

Monday, September 14, 2015

Synopsis

This document is an analysis and visualization of the responses to the client feedback survey.

The Comments were reviewed in batches to uncover patterns via categorization. The Categories of the Responses include Accuracy, Courtesy, Payment Frequency, Price, Availability, Hours, Location, Positive, and Negative. The Comments were scored for Response Category, with consideration for more than one Response Category per Comment.

Through processing of the Data, in the R programming language, was performed to extract the conclusions in this Document. Most of the R coding was left out of the rendering of this Document, in order to increase comprehensibility.

The sections of this Document include:
1) Data import
2) Data Summary
3) Client Feedback Survey Overview
4) Customer Analysis
5) Response Analysis Plots
6) Survey Response WordClouds

Importing survey response data tables:

dt <- read.csv("clientfeedback.csv", check.names=F)

Client Feedback Survey Overview:

There are 10 questions in the client feedback survey.

The number of clients that responded to the survey is 249.

The client feedback survey asked the following 10 questions:

What led you to DexaFit?
What did you enjoy learning most during your visit with us?
How are you using the feedback from your tests to improve your fitness and health?
Do you prefer to pay for your testing in full in one payment or in installments over a period of months?
Other
How often would you like to test throughout the year if we offered a simple monthly payment plan?
How would you describe us to a friend?
Do you have any big questions, roadblocks, concerns, or ideas?
Whats your favorite website for fitness and nutrition?
Whats your email address?
